text: Alexa Guarachi and Desirae Krawczyk were the defending champions, but Krawczyk chose not to participate. Guarachi played alongside Erin Routliffe, but lost in the first round to Cornelia Lister and Renata Voráčová. Anastasia Potapova and Yana Sizikova won the title, defeating Monique Adamczak and Han Xinyun in the final, 6–2, 6–4. ==Seeds== ==Draw== ===Draw=== ==References== *Main Draw Ladies Open Lausanne - Doubles Category:WTA Swiss Open
title: 2019 Ladies Open Lausanne – Doubles
